rom GPT-Neo TinyStories to a similarly small GPT-NeoX/Pythia-style checkpoint or a minimal in-repo causal transformer. Record that the base model changed before collecting final results.\ndocs/11_FAILURE_MODES_AND_PIVOTS.md:15:## Sampler drifts downhill at intermediate checkpoints\ndocs/11_FAILURE_MODES_AND_PIVOTS.md:17:Increase localization, test the predeclared `n_beta` alternatives, and inspect center loss. If no common configuration works across early/middle/late checkpoints, do not report comparable LLC. Pivot to:\ndocs/11_FAILURE_MODES_AND_PIVOTS.md:19:1. a controlled micro-language where checkpoints can be trained closer to plateaus;\ndocs/11_FAILURE_MODES_AND_PIVOTS.md:25:Do not force a changepoint. Increase checkpoint density only under the predeclared adaptive rule. If behavior remains smooth, report the null or pivot to a controlled Portuguese-like grammar with held-out compositions.\ndocs/11_FAILURE_MODES_AND_PIVOTS.md:37:Profile data loading and evaluation callbacks; cache tokenized data; reduce checkpoint serialization frequency while preserving milestone checkpoints; test sequence length 64; ensure GPU is used. Do not scale up until one trajectory is comfortably below one hour.\ndocs/11_FAILURE_MODES_AND_PIVOTS.md:41:Keep optimizer state only at recovery checkpoints; save weights at analysis checkpoints; compress logs; upload/download artifacts; never silently delete the only copy of a run.\ndocs/01_RESEARCH_PROTOCOL.md:17:Final model: `roneneldan/TinyStories-8M`.\ndocs/01_RESEARCH_PROTOCOL.md:19:At runtime, record exact parameter counts rather than assuming the names are exact counts. Preserve the original tokenizer and architecture. The initial checkpoint should be an English-trained causal LM. No instruction tuning is needed.\ndocs/01_RESEARCH_PROTOCOL.md:25:Initial final configuration:\ndocs/01_RESEARCH_PROTOCOL.md:32:| Target tokens/trajectory | 8 million |\ndocs/01_RESEARCH_PROTOCOL.md:36:| Initial final LR | 1e-4, subject to pilot |\ndocs/01_RE