 the required repair touches VM lifecycle/driver state controlled outside the GPU worker. This is not a spend approval issue; it is an operator-side infrastructure intervention required before any pilot or final run can be scientifically valid.\nstate/decision_log.md:159:planner escalated to a human: AGENTS.md forbids moving past infrastructure before CUDA, VRAM headroom, and the train-save-reload-evaluate-sample loop pass. The executive plan makes infrastructure the first decisive gate. The current state already contains repeated blocked infrastructure diagnostics and identifies an operator-side driver/device-node failure; the executor cannot repair VM lifecycle or driver state from the worker. Further pilot/final/LLC work would violate gate order, so a human/operator infrastructure action is required before useful bounded executor work can continue.\nstate/decision_log.md:175:Decision: proceed to the scientific pilot gate; do not launch a final scientific run. The fresh run used\nstate/decision_log.md:183:records a complete train-save-reload-evaluate-sample loop with checkpoint hashes and generated sample.\nstate/decision_log.md:210:Decision: proceed, recorded as a structured gate decision; do not launch TinyStories-8M in this tick.\nstate/decision_log.md:214:Implementation: added `scripts/scientific_pilot.py` and `tests/test_scientific_pilot.py`, committed as\nstate/decision_log.md:221:`results/01_scientific_pilot/scientific_pilot_20260620T053047Z/data_splits/split_manifest.json`.\nstate/decision_log.md:225:Evidence: `results/01_scientific_pilot/scientific_pilot_20260620T053047Z/gate_decision.json`,\nstate/decision_log.md:227:checkpoint trees with hashes under each condition, and early/middle/late sampler traces under\nstate/decision_log.md:231:4.1498. Shuffled Portuguese final BPB was 4.3511, leaving a 0.2013 BPB structured-vs-shuffled gap.\nstate/decision_log.md:232:Matched English BPB changed from 2.6944 to 2.7762. The final structured grammar probe reported 0.8\nstate/decision_log.md:242:not the final 8M trajectory. The grammar evidence is a pilot probe plus constructed sanity checks, and\nstate/decision_log.md:245:before TinyStories-8M.\nscripts/tinystories_gate_loop.py:66:    checkpoint_dir = args.output_dir / \"checkpoint\"\nscripts/tinystories_gate_loop.py:107:    model.save_pretrained(checkpoint_dir, safe_serialization=True)\nscripts/tinystories_gate_loop.py:108:    tokenizer.save_pretrained(checkpoint_dir)\nscripts/tinystories_gate_loop.py:114:    reloaded = AutoModelForCausalLM.from_pretrained(checkpoint_dir).to(device).eval()\nscripts/tinystories_gate_loop.py:152:        \"checkpoint_dir\": str(checkpoint_dir),\nscripts/tinystories_gate_loop.py:153:        \"checkpoint_hashes_sha256\": hash_tree(checkpoint_dir),\ncodex/prompts/01_scientific_pilot.md:3:Build immutable small data splits, structured/shuffled conditions, BPB, grammar-margin evaluation, English retention, checkpointing, and manifests. Run the predeclared short LR pilot and early/middle/late sampler cross-check. Launch long commands through the bounded runner. Preserve failures and chain traces. Update state and registry files.\ncodex/prompts/01_scientific_pilot.md:5:Do not add Spanish or broad localization. Do not proceed to 8M until the pilot gates in `AGENTS.md` are demonstrably satisfied and recorded as a structured gate decision. Under unattended orchestration, the operator's pre-authorization (see \"Unattended autonomous operation\" in `AGENTS.md`) stands in for per-run human approval, bounded by the hard budget cap and the wall-clock deadline.\nstate/experiment_registry.csv:7:scientific_pilot_20260620T053047Z,01_scientific_pilot,passed,structured_pt__shuffled_pt__matched_en,roneneldan/TinyStories-3M,20260620,5c3cd8e493b0d9c9a0be0b748e8b66e3eadbed44,,2026-06-20T05:30:47Z,2026-06-20T05:31:37Z,0.0125,0.0125,results/01_scientific_pilot/scientific_pilot_20260620T053047Z,\"Bounded TinyStories-3M scientific pilot passed with structured gate decision proceed: immutable OPUS-100 en-pt splits and shuffled-token mapping hashed; LR pilot selected 3e-4; structured PT BPB 6.4532->4.1498; shuffled PT final BPB 4.3511; matched English BPB 2.6944->2.7762; grammar accuracy 0.8/mean margin 0.5566 with sanity checks passed; early/middle/late fixed-config LLC zarr traces preserved; no 8M launched.\"\ndocs/04_BENCHMARKS_AND_FERMI_ESTIMATES.md:5:Tiny models do not necessarily achieve high hardware utilization. Python overhead, data loading, checkpoint writes, observer evaluations, and many small kernels can dominate. FLOP-only estimates are therefore less trustworthy than two short end-to-end measurements.\ndocs/04_BENCHMARKS_AND_FERMI_ESTIMATES.md:14:4. record mean, median, p95, tokens/second, peak VRAM, CPU utilization, and checkpoint-write time;\ndocs/04_BENCHMARKS_AND_FERMI_ESTIMATES.md:21:At one pilot checkpoint:\ndocs/04_BENCHMARKS_AND_FERMI_ESTIMATES.md:34:For 8 million target tokens, sequence length 128, and global batch 32:\ndocs/04_BENCHMARKS_AND_FERMI_ESTIMATES.md:40:Four final trajectories require about 7,812 optimizer steps. Add roughly 2,500 steps for pilots, LR trials, failed starts, and one optional branch:\ndocs/04_BENCHMARKS_AND_FERMI_ESTIMATES.md:98:One 8M training trajectory should generally be minutes, not ten hours. A ten-hour single trajectory is a signal that the pipeline/model choice is wrong for this sprint.\ndocs/04_BENCHMARKS_AND_FERMI_ESTIMATES.md:118:- reduce LLC checkpoint density;\ncodex/schemas/plan_directive.schema.json:16:        \"scientific_pilot\",\ncodex/schemas/plan_directive.schema.json:17:        \"final_training\",\ncodex/schemas/plan_directive.schema.json:25:      \"description\": \"Path (repo-relative) to the executor prompt the harness should run for this stage, e.g. codex/prompts/01_scientific_pilot.md or codex/prompts/diagnose_and_fix.md.\"\ncodex/schemas/plan_directive.schema.json:34:      \"description\": \"Wall-clock budget granted to the execution agent for this tick. Small for early exploration, generous for the final run (e.g. ~6h for a ~3.5h run). The harness clamps this to the time remaining before the overall deadline.\"\ntests/test_scientific_pilot.py:7:from scripts.scientific_pilot import (\ntests/test_scientific_pilot.py:68:    def test_checkpoint_schedule_includes_start_and_end(self) -> None:\ntests/test_scientific_pilot.py:91:        self.assertEqual(cfg.checkpoint_steps[0], 0)\ntests/test_scientific_pilot.py:92:        self.assertEqual(cfg.checkpoint_steps[-1], 6)\ncodex/orchestrate.py:216:    final_json = out_dir / \"final_decision.json\"\ncodex/orchestrate.py:230:        \"OUT\": str(final_json),\ncodex/orchestrate.py:249:    return read_json(final_json)\ncodex/orchestrate.py:280:        stage = \"diagnose_and_fix\" if (self.name == \"retry\" and failed) else \"scientific_pilot\"\ncodex/orchestrate.py:284:            \"executor_prompt\": f\"codex/prompts/{'diagnose_and_fix' if stage=='diagnose_and_fix' else '01_scientific_pilot'}.md\",\ncodex/orchestrate.py:326:                f\"dryrun-{self.name}-{tick}\", \"scientific_pilot\", status, \"structured_portuguese\",\nscripts/scientific_pilot.py:84:    def checkpoint_steps(self) -> list[int]:\nscripts/scientific_pilot.py:101:            \"checkpoint_steps\": self.checkpoint_steps,\nscripts/scientific_pilot.py:357:    write_json(split_dir / \"split_manifest.json\", manifest)\nscripts/scientific_pilot.py:619:def save_checkpoint(model: Any, tokenizer: Any, optimizer: Any, checkpoint_dir: Path, metadata: dict[str, Any]) -> dict[str, Any]:\nscripts/scientific_pilot.py:622:    checkpoint_dir.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\nscripts/scientific_pilot.py:623:    model.save_pretrained(checkpoint_dir, safe_serialization=True)\nscripts/scientific_pilot.py:624:    tokenizer.save_pretrained(checkpoint_dir)\nscripts/scientific_pilot.py:625:    torch.save(optimizer.state_dict(), checkpoint_dir / \"optimizer.pt\")\nscripts/scientific_pilot.py:626:    write_json(checkpoint_dir / \"checkpoint_metadata.json\", metadata)\nscripts/scientific_pilot.py:627:    return hash_tree(checkpoint_dir)\nscripts/scientific_pilot.py:688:            \"final_pt_bpb\": after[\"pt_validation\"][\"bpb\"],\nscripts/scientific_pilot.py:691:            \"final_english_bpb\": after[\"english_retention\"][\"bpb\"],\nscripts/scientific_pilot.py:694:            \"final_grammar_mean_margin\": after[\"grammar_margin\"][\"mean_margin\"],\nscripts/scientific_pilot.py:705:        if math.isfinite(float(item[\"final_pt_bpb\"]))\nscripts/scientific_pilot.py:709:    selected = min(finite or results, key=lambda item: (float(item[\"final_pt_bpb\"]), item[\"learning_rate\"]))\nscripts/scientific_pilot.py:712:        \"selection_rule\": \"Choose the finite LR with improved Portuguese validation BPB and no >50% or >0.25 absolute English BPB degradation; rank by final Portuguese BPB then lower LR.\",\nscripts/scientific_pilot.py:750:    checkpoint_root = condition_dir / \"checkpoints\"\nscripts/scientific_pilot.py:755:    checkpoint_hashes: dict[str, dict[str, str]] = {}\nscripts/scientific_pilot.py:758:    steps_to_save = cfg.checkpoint_steps\nscripts/scientific_pilot.py:780:        checkpoint_name = f\"step_{step:06d}\"\nscripts/scientific_pilot.py:783:        evaluations[checkpoint_name] = {\nscripts/scientific_pilot.py:789:        write_json(eval_dir / f\"{checkpoint_name}.json\", evaluations[checkpoint_name])\nscripts/scientific_pilot.py:790:        hashes = save_checkpoint(\nscripts/scientific_pilot.py:794:            checkpoint_root / checkpoint_name,\nscripts/scientific_pilot.py:804:        checkpoint_hashes[checkpoint_name] = hashes\nscripts/scientific_pilot.py:809:        \"checkpoint_steps\": steps_to_save,\nscripts/scientific_pilot.py:813:        \"checkpoint_hashes_sha256\": checkpoint_hashes,\nscripts/scientific_pilot.py:814:        \"checkpoint_root\": str(checkpoint_root),\nscripts/scientific_pilot.py:904:    checkpoints = structured_summary[\"checkpoint_steps\"]\nscripts/scientific_pilot.py:905:    selected_steps = sorted({checkpoints[0], checkpoints[len(checkpoints) // 2], checkpoints[-1]})\nscripts/scientific_pilot.py:909:        checkpoint_name = f\"step_{step:06d}\"\nscripts/scientific_pilot.py:910:        checkpoint_dir = Path(structured_summary[\"checkpoint_root\"]) / checkpoint_name\nscripts/scientific_pilot.py:911:        model = AutoModelForCausalLM.from_pretrained(checkpoint_dir).to(cfg.device).float().train()\nscripts/scientific_pilot.py:912:        trace_output = llc_dir / f\"{checkpoint_name}.zarr\"\nscripts/scientific_pilot.py:948:            \"checkpoint\": checkpoint_name,\nscripts/scientific_pilot.py:963:        write_json(llc_dir / f\"{checkpoint_name}.json\", item)\nscripts/scientific_pilot.py:969:        \"selection\": \"Predeclared early/middle/late structured Portuguese checkpoints from the pilot schedule.\",\nscripts/scientific_pilot.py:977:        \"warning\": \"Pilot LLC cross-check is diagnostic only; it is not a reportable final SLT phase-transition claim.\",\nscripts/scientific_pilot.py:996:    first_name = f\"step_{cfg.checkpoint_steps[0]:06d}\"\nscripts/scientific_pilot.py:997:    last_name = f\"step_{cfg.checkpoint_steps[-1]:06d}\"\nscripts/scientific_pilot.py:999:    pt_final = structured[last_name][\"pt_validation\"][\"bpb\"]\nscripts/scientific_pilot.py:1000:    shuffled_final = shuffled[last_name][\"pt_validation\"][\"bpb\"]\nscripts/scientific_pilot.py:1002:    english_final = english[last_name][\"english_retention\"][\"bpb\"]\nscripts/scientific_pilot.py:1003:    grammar_final = structured[last_name][\"grammar_margin\"]\nscripts/scientific_pilot.py:1004:    structured_vs_shuffled_gap = shuffled_final - pt_final\nscripts/scientific_pilot.py:1007:        \"data_manifest\": str(output_dir / \"data_splits\" / \"split_manifest.json\"),\nscripts/scientific_pilot.py:1016:        \"portuguese_validation_improves\": pt_final < pt_initial,\nscripts/scientific_pilot.py:1017:        \"grammar_probe_above_chance_or_sanity_passes\": grammar_final[\"accuracy\"] > 0.5 or grammar_sanity[\"passed\"],\nscripts/scientific_pilot.py:1026:        next_action = \"Record pilot pass, then ask the planner for the next bounded gate; do not launch TinyStories-8M in this tick.\"\nscripts/scientific_pilot.py:1029:        next_action = \"Apply the behavioral-control pivot: increase pilot data/steps or strengthen shuffled-control diagnostics before any 8M run.\"\nscripts/scientific_pilot.py:1032:        next_action = \"Apply the sampler pivot in docs/11_FAILURE_MODES_AND_PIVOTS.md before any 8M run.\"\nscripts/scientific_pilot.py:1035:        next_action = \"Stop before 8M and diagnose failed pilot criteria.\"\nscripts/scientific_pilot.py:1037:        \"phase\": \"01_scientific_pilot\",\nscripts/scientific_pilot.py:1042:            \"structured_pt_final_bpb\": pt_final,\nscripts/scientific_pilot.py:1043:            \"structured_pt_bpb_delta\": pt_final - pt_initial,\nscripts/scientific_pilot.py:1044:            \"shuffled_pt_final_bpb\": shuffled_final,\nscripts/scientific_pilot.py:1047:            \"matched_english_final_bpb\": english_final,\nscripts/scientific_pilot.py:1048:            \"matched_english_bpb_delta\": english_final - english_initial,\nscripts/scientific_pilot.py:1049:            \"structured_final_grammar_accuracy\": grammar_final[\"accuracy\"],\nscripts/scientific_pilot.py:1050:            \"structured_final_grammar_mean_margin\": grammar_final[\"mean_margin\"],\nscripts/scientific_pilot.py:1057:            \"This is a short TinyStories-3M pilot, not the final 8M trajectory.\",\nscripts/scientific_pilot.py:1062:            \"Small OPUS stream prefix may not represent the final corpus distribution.\",\nscripts/scientific_pilot.py:1199:        \"run_kind\": \"tinystories_3m_scientific_pilot\",\nscripts/scientific_pilot.py:1227:    write_json(data[\"split_dir\"] / \"split_manifest.json\", data[\"manifest\"])\nscripts/scientific_pilot.py:1264:            \"data_split_manifest\": str(data[\"split_dir\"] / \"split_manifest.json\"),\ncodex/README.md:9:The wrapper writes a JSONL event log and a final structured decision. It defaults to `workspace-write`. Set `CODEX_SANDBOX=danger-full-access CONFIRM_DANGER=YES` only on the isolated worker when system-level access is genuinely necessary.\ncodex/run_phase.sh:21:  -o \"$OUT_DIR/final_decision.json\" \\\ndocs/09_FAKE_REPORT_WALKTHROUGH.md:46:The fake report localizes a susceptibility increase to a final MLP and freezes that component before the transition. The freeze delays grammar more than a matched control freeze. This is moderately good causal evidence, but capacity reduction remains a confound.\ndocs/09_FAKE_REPORT_WALKTHROUGH.md:48:The final interpretation explicitly rejects three stronger claims:\ndocs/09_FAKE_REPORT_WALKTHROUGH.md:58:- stable SGLD at transient checkpoints;\ndocs/09_FAKE_REPORT_WALKTHROUGH.md:69:| `synthetic_training_trajectories.csv` | merged checkpoint behavior metrics |\ndocs/09_FAKE_REPORT_WALKTHROUGH.md:71:| `synthetic_condition_summary.csv` | real final checkpoint aggregation |\ndocs/09_FAKE_REPORT_WALKTHROUGH.md:73:| `figure_1c_llc_trajectory.png` | chain-level LLC aggregation |\nresults/_codex/exec-final_training-003/prompt.md:1:Read `AGENTS.md` and verify that the scientific pilot passed and explicit human approval is recorded in the decision log. Freeze configs and data hashes. Run final behavioral trajectories in priority order: Portuguese seed A, shuffled Portuguese, matched English, Portuguese seed B. Use bounded jobs and checkpoint by target tokens. Evaluate every checkpoint and update the cost projection after each trajectory.\nresults/_codex/exec-final_training-003/prompt.md:3:Do not inspect or optimize final LLC until behavior outputs and checkpoint selection rules are frozen. Stop if the projected total exceeds the hard budget or runtime gate.\nresults/_codex/exec-final_training-003/prompt.md:9:- Task: Proceed from the passed TinyStories-3M pilot gate to the TinyStories-8M final full-parameter continued-pretraining run. Before launch, verify the committed state records passed infrastructure and pilot gates, immutable split manifests/hashes are available, cached model/data/tokenizer dependencies are usable without internet, and the manifest records the current git commit. Launch only through `infra/remote/run_bounded_job.sh` with a bounded runtime, status/log/exit-code artifacts, and no cloud lifecycle actions. Run the minimum real final trajectories: structured Portuguese seed 1, structured Portuguese seed 2, token-shuffled Portuguese, and matched English, with behavioral BPB/grammar evaluation at every saved checkpoint and checkpoint hashes recorded. Success criterion: a restartable `results/02_final_training/<run_id>/` contains manifests, logs, exit codes, checkpoint hashes, per-checkpoint behavioral metrics for all required conditions, updated `state/current_status.json`, `state/decision_log.md`, `state/experiment_registry.csv`, and a committed gate decision identifying the checkpoint subset for LLC.\ndocs/07_ADAPTION_AUTOSCIENTIST_ASSESSMENT.md:7:That is potentially useful for ordinary training-recipe or data optimization. The public page does not establish the controls required for this SLT experiment: raw frequent checkpoint export, full-parameter training, exact tokenizer retention, deterministic data order/seeds, arbitrary custom evaluation callbacks, optimizer-state export, or custom `devinterp` execution.\ndocs/07_ADAPTION_AUTOSCIENTIST_ASSESSMENT.md:24:| Frequent checkpoints | export at specified cumulative-token milestones |\ndocs/07_ADAPTION_AUTOSCIENTIST_ASSESSMENT.md:29:| Custom code | can execute arbitrary Python or at least allow checkpoints to move to GCP |\ndocs/07_ADAPTION_AUTOSCIENTIST_ASSESSMENT.md:34:- no raw checkpoint export;\ndocs/07_ADAPTION_AUTOSCIENTIST_ASSESSMENT.md:35:- only final model export;\ndocs/07_ADAPTION_AUTOSCIENTIST_ASSESSMENT.md:43:AutoScientist advertises co-optimization of data and recipe against a desired outcome. If that desired outcome is the same grammar metric used to claim a developmental transition, the system can overfit the evaluation or select a trajectory because it looks transition-like. This creates strong researcher/optimizer degrees of freedom.\ndocs/07_ADAPTION_AUTOSCIENTIST_ASSESSMENT.md:51:5. rerun the confirmatory trajectory from scratch on GCP with full logging and checkpoints;\ndocs/07_ADAPTION_AUTOSCIENTIST_ASSESSMENT.md:58:- producing an auxiliary optimized Portuguese checkpoint;\ndocs/07_ADAPTION_AUTOSCIENTIST_ASSESSMENT.md:63:- the sole source of training checkpoints;\ndocs/07_ADAPTION_AUTOSCIENTIST_ASSESSMENT.md:64:- performing opaque automatic training whose trajectory cannot be reconstructed;\ndocs/02_SLT_BAYESIAN_COMPLICATIONS.md:5:The continued-pretraining optimizer remains ordinary AdamW. SLT enters through a second procedure that samples a localized posterior around selected checkpoints. In schematic form:\ndocs/02_SLT_BAYESIAN_COMPLICATIONS.md:13:where the checkpoint is the center, the empirical loss and reference dataset define the measured geometry, `n_beta` controls effective inverse temperature, and localization controls how far the sampler can move.\ndocs/02_SLT_BAYESIAN_COMPLICATIONS.md:19:### Intermediate checkpoints may not be local minima\ndocs/02_SLT_BAYESIAN_COMPLICATIONS.md:21:The clean theoretical object is associated with local geometry near minima of a population loss. A checkpoint halfway through Portuguese adaptation can have an obvious downhill direction on Portuguese loss. A localized chain can therefore drift toward a better point rather than equilibrate around the checkpoint.\ndocs/02_SLT_BAYESIAN_COMPLICATIONS.md:23:Inspect whether sampled loss rises from the baseline, reaches a stable range, and remains localized. Persistent loss below the center or monotonic downhill movement is a rejection signal. Increasing localization or adjusting effective temperature may help, but a checkpoint that never admits a stable common protocol should not produce a headline LLC number.\ndocs/02_SLT_BAYESIAN_COMPLICATIONS.md:31:The three primary knobs are sampler learning rate, `n_beta`, and localization. Burn-in, draw spacing, chain count, draw count, batch size, and preconditioner also matter. A configuration that looks good at one checkpoint may fail elsewhere.\ndocs/02_SLT_BAYESIAN_COMPLICATIONS.md:35:#### Coarse sweep on one middle checkpoint\ndocs/02_SLT_BAYESIAN_COMPLICATIONS.md:47:#### Cross-check across trajectory\ndocs/02_SLT_BAYESIAN_COMPLICATIONS.md:49:Take the two or three most plausible configurations and test each at early, middle, and late checkpoints using two chains and longer traces.\ndocs/02_SLT_BAYESIAN_COMPLICATIONS.md:59:- behavior is acceptable at all three checkpoints.\ndocs/02_SLT_BAYESIAN_COMPLICATIONS.md:84:- changepoint uncertainty due to checkpoint spacing;\ndocs/02_SLT_BAYESIAN_COMPLICATIONS.md:99:Small Langevin updates and injected noise make numerical behavior important. Begin with FP32 sampling. BF16 training is acceptable only if it materially improves benchmark time and produces equivalent short-pilot behavior. Keep an FP32 copy of checkpoints for sampling when feasible.\ndocs/02_SLT_BAYESIAN_COMPLICATIONS.md:103:A training-trajectory changepoint in an estimated LLC is not automatically a formal Bayesian phase transition. Use cautious terms:\ndocs/02_SLT_BAYESIAN_COMPLICATIONS.md:112:A sampler step is roughly a training-like gradient step, but the campaign multiplies steps by chains, checkpoints, and tuning configurations. A plausible campaign contains about 31,700 chain steps versus about 10,000 ordinary training/pilot steps. SGLD is therefore likely to dominate cost even though the model is tiny.\ndocs/05_CODEX_GCP_OPERATIONS.md:19:- final artifact download.\ndocs/05_CODEX_GCP_OPERATIONS.md:30:- checkpoints, traces, logs, figures, and run manifests.\ndocs/05_CODEX_GCP_OPERATIONS.md:60:./codex/run_phase.sh codex/prompts/01_scientific_pilot.md\ndocs/05_CODEX_GCP_OPERATIONS.md:86:  -- python -m experiments.train --config configs/final_pt_seed_a.yaml\ndocs/05_CODEX_GCP_OPERATIONS.md:106:Human gates remain appropriate for final-run launch, budget expansion, scientific scope changes, and publication.\ndocs/05_CODEX_GCP_OPERATIONS.md:116:The local machine is sufficient for report writing, data filtering prototypes, unit tests, and tiny CPU smoke tests. The final campaign benefits materially from a GPU because full-parameter training is repeated and SGLD requires tens of thousands of gradient-equivalent steps. A CPU-only run may be technically possible for 3M parameters but is a poor use of a three-day sprint.\ndocs/00_EXECUTIVE_PLAN.md:7:The model is trained conventionally with AdamW. At selected checkpoints, training stops conceptually: the checkpoint is frozen as a center point, and a separate localized Bayesian sampler probes the nearby loss geometry. This means the training loop itself does not need to become Bayesian, but the entire checkpoint, reference-data, sampler-tuning, diagnostics, and analysis protocol must be designed before the final run.\ndocs/00_EXECUTIVE_PLAN.md:15:- TinyStories-3M pilot; TinyStories-8M final.\ndocs/00_EXECUTIVE_PLAN.md:20:- Behavioral evaluation at approximately eleven log-spaced checkpoints.\ndocs/00_EXECUTIVE_PLAN.md:21:- Full LLC trajectory for the first Portuguese seed, reduced LLC replication for the second seed and controls.\ndocs/00_EXECUTIVE_PLAN.md:31:Intermediate Portuguese checkpoints may not behave like local minima of the Portuguese empirical loss. A localized SGLD chain can drift downhill rather than equilibrate around the checkpoint. If no common localization/temperature configuration yields stable traces across early, middle, and late checkpoints, the intended LLC comparison is not valid. This is a go/no-go gate, not a plot-cleaning problem.\ndocs/00_EXECUTIVE_PLAN.md:37:| One final continued-pretraining trajectory | 15 minutes | 5–35 minutes |\ndocs/00_EXECUTIVE_PLAN.md:39:| Sampler tuning and final LLC campaign | 5 GPU-hours | 2.5–11 |\ndocs/00_EXECUTIVE_PLAN.md:44:These are Fermi estimates. Replace them with benchmark measurements before the final campaign.\ndocs/00_EXECUTIVE_PLAN.md:48:Use a GCP `g2-standard-4` VM with one NVIDIA L4 and 24 GB GPU memory in a G2-capable US zone, initially `us-central1-a`. São Paulo GCP zones list T4 rather than G2. Use on-demand capacity for final runs. RunPod is a contingency if GCP quota or capacity becomes a blocker, but this handoff automates GCP because the operator already has billing configured.\ndocs/00_EXECUTIVE_PLAN.md:57:2. **Scientific pilot:** structured Portuguese improves, grammar probes pass sanity checks, shuffled control behaves differently, and one common sampler configuration works at three checkpoints.\ndocs/00_EXECUTIVE_PLAN.md:58:3. **Final campaign:** only after the first two gates, run the 8M trajectories and reportable LLC estimates.\ndocs/03_THREE_DAY_EXECUTION_PLAN.md:12:4. Run 100 training steps, save checkpoint, reload, compare loss.\ndocs/03_THREE_DAY_EXECUTION_PLAN.md:32:Use TinyStories-3M and 0.5–1 million target tokens.\ndocs/03_THREE_DAY_EXECUTION_PLAN.md:36:3. Run one structured and one shuffled trajectory.\ndocs/03_THREE_DAY_EXECUTION_PLAN.md:38:5. Test the best two or three sampler configurations at early, middle, and late checkpoints.\ndocs/03_THREE_DAY_EXECUTION_PLAN.md:46:- one common sampler configuration works across three checkpoints;\ndocs/03_THREE_DAY_EXECUTION_PLAN.md:47:- a final 8M campaign still fits the budget.\ndocs/03_THREE_DAY_EXECUTION_PLAN.md:51:## Phase 2: final behavior trajectories\ndocs/03_THREE_DAY_EXECUTION_PLAN.md:60:Evaluate every checkpoint as soon as it is saved. The first main seed and controls create a coherent minimum report even if replication is reduced.\ndocs/03_THREE_DAY_EXECUTION_PLAN.md:62:Freeze all data, checkpoint, and behavior outputs before inspecting the final LLC trajectory.\ndocs/03_THREE_DAY_EXECUTION_PLAN.md:68:1. main Portuguese seed A at five fixed checkpoints;\ndocs/03_THREE_DAY_EXECUTION_PLAN.md:69:2. two behavior-bracketing checkpoints;\ndocs/03_THREE_DAY_EXECUTION_PLAN.md:77:If time becomes scarce, remove Spanish, broad component localization, and dense control checkpoints before removing diagnostics or the shuffled control.\ndocs/03_THREE_DAY_EXECUTION_PLAN.md:83:- behavioral trajectory figure;\ndocs/03_THREE_DAY_EXECUTION_PLAN.md:84:- LLC trajectory with chain uncertainty;\ndocs/03_THREE_DAY_EXECUTION_PLAN.md:86:- final-condition table;\ndocs/03_THREE_DAY_EXECUTION_PLAN.md:87:- seed/checkpoint changepoint table;\ndocs/03_THREE_DAY_EXECUTION_PLAN.md:89:- explicit limitations on transient checkpoints and sampler sensitivity.\ndocs/03_THREE_DAY_EXECUTION_PLAN.md:107:- beginning the final 8M campaign;\ndocs/03_THREE_DAY_EXECUTION_PLAN.md:119:3. reduce second-seed LLC to three checkpoints;\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
